data.title: Tracey Carrington - Women's Basketball
data.meta_description: Tracey Carrington (10) Guard  - 2012-13 (Sophomore): Named captain of the team…Played in 31 games, making 28 starts...Averaged 10.7 points per game to rank second
data.text:
2012-13 (Sophomore): Named captain of the team…Played in 31 games, making 28 starts...Averaged 10.7 points per game to rank second on the team and tied Bianca Jarrett for a team-leading 5.4 rebounds per outing…Also recorded 39 assists, 31 steals and five blocks…Shot 81.4 percent (83-of-102) from the free throw line…Reached double figures in scoring 18 times and rebounding twice…Had one double-double on the season...Totaled 12 points, four rebounds, three steals against Howard (3/14) in a MEAC Quarterfinal game…Finished with 17 points on 7-of-12 shooting and had seven rebounds against Maryland Eastern Shore (3/11) in the MEAC Tournament opener…Shot a career-high 8-of-13 for 16 points, grabbed seven rebounds and had three steals at North Carolina Central (1/28)…Notched 10 rebounds, eight points and had three steals against Army (1/6)…Tied a career-high with 21 points and grabbed 13 rebounds to record a double-double in the MEAC opener against Coppin State (12/3). Also shot a perfect 7-for-7 from the free throw line and added two steals and a block…Totaled a then career-high 21 points, five rebounds, two steals, two assist and a block at Cornell (12/1)…Shot 7-of-9 from the field for 16 points, had seven rebounds, a block, a steal and an assist against Columbia (11/23)…Fell shy of a double-double with 11 points and nine rebounds in the season-opener against Maryland Baltimore County (11/9).

2011-12 (Freshman): Named to the MEAC All-Rookie Team…Averaged 7.5 points and ranked third on the team in rebounding with 5.3 boards per outing…Played in 24 games, making four starts…Scored eight points, grabbed five rebounds, had a block and an assist against NC A&T (3/5)…Fell shy of a double-double with nine points and 10 rebounds at Delaware State (2/27)…Totaled 11 points and had a team-high seven rebounds at Coppin State (2/22)…Scored a team-high 10 points, grabbed four rebounds, had two assists and a game-high three steals against Maryland Eastern Shore (2/11)…Finished with a team-high 14 points and added three assists and two rebounds against Coppin State (2/4)…Notched 13 points, eight rebounds and a game-high five assists against North Carolina Central (1/23)…Was short of a double-double, scoring 15 points and pulling down nine rebounds against North Carolina A&T (1/21)…Finished with 15 points and six rebounds against Norfolk State (1/14)…Scored 10 points and had eight rebounds at Arkansas (12/19)…Totaled 13 points on 9-of-9 from the charity stripe, seven rebounds and a steal at Missouri State (12/18)…Had a game-high five steals, six points, three rebounds and two assists at Bucknell (11/22)…Tallied 10 points, seven rebounds and an assist at George Washington (11/16)…Made her Morgan State debut in the season-opener at Maryland Baltimore County (11/11) and scored 10 points, had four rebounds and an assist.

High School: Was a three-year letterwinner at Dundalk High...Was an all-metro first-team pick by the Baltimore Sun as a senior, who averaged 27.0 points, 14.0 rebounds, 2.3 assists and 2.5 steals per game...Finished her career with 1,615 points, 727 rebounds and 97 blocks....Helped the Eagles to a 1A/2A Division title as a senior...Scored 30 or more points eight times, 20 or more 18 times and had a season high of 43 points...Scored 36 points against Baltimore City in a regional quarterfinal loss...Earned back-to-back second-team all-metro honors as a sophomore and junior...Won the Dundalk Eagles’ Player of the Year award as a junior and senior...Played in the Maryland vs. Pennsylvania all-star game and the Baltimore County vs. Baltimore City all-star game...Coached by Cynthia Vetri...Was on the honor roll.

Personal: Born on July 19, 1993 in Baltimore, Md....Daughter of Alisa Brice...Major is sociology with a minor in criminal justice.
